<seg id="1"> Mom of Ten Years Ago </seg>
</hl>
<poster>
<seg id="2"> Helen Li </seg>
</poster>
<seg id="3"> Read this article, and wanted to share it with people. </seg>
<seg id="4"> This is not an impulsion, but warmness and kindness staying in my heart for a long time. </seg>
<seg id="5"> I ask myself if it were me, what I would do. </seg>
<seg id="6"> The answer is very clear. I would hang up the phone, "You dialed a wrong number." </seg>
<seg id="7"> This year I have been thinking about what really counts for helping people. </seg>
<seg id="8"> I have given up tentative conduct, such as donations of cash or items. </seg>
<seg id="9"> Some friend said a couple of days ago that he has no time to take care of himself, not mention to help people, even though his desire for providing help is bigger than his ability. </seg>
<seg id="10"> Wish you a happy day :) </seg>
<seg id="11"> Helen </seg>
<seg id="12"> Mom of Ten Years Ago </seg>
<seg id="13"> It was one day ten years ago when this teacher was taking a nap by using the rest time at noon. Suddenly, the phone rang. </seg>
<seg id="14"> She picked up the phone, and heard a strange and rude voice: "Your child stole a book, and we caught her. Come and hurry up!" </seg>
<seg id="15"> The crying noise of a little girl and denouncing voices from others came out of the handset. </seg>
<seg id="16"> She understood the thing immediately when she turned her head and looked at her only daughter, who was watching TV. </seg>
<seg id="17"> There must be a little girl who was caught by the saleswoman for stealing a book. She does not want her family members to know this, so she made up a phone number, and a phone call happens to come here. </seg>
<seg id="18"> She could of course hang up the phone and give no response, and even scold the other side. </seg>
<seg id="19"> Because this thing has nothing to do with her. </seg>
<seg id="20"> But she herself is a teacher; maybe that girl is one of her pupils. </seg>
<seg id="21"> She could probably imagine through the phone that that little girl, who made a wrong decision at that moment, must be very panicked, and may be facing the most terrible situation of her life. </seg>
<seg id="22"> After she hesitated for a moment, she suddenly had an idea in her mind. Yes, I will do it this way. </seg>
<seg id="23"> Then, she asked for the detailed address of the bookstore, and hurried there. </seg>
<seg id="24"> As she expected, a little girl with tear stains all over her face was standing in the bookstore. </seg>
<seg id="25"> And those adults standing around were scolding her ferociously in loud voices. </seg>
<seg id="26"> She rushed to the poor little girl and held her in her arms, and turned her head to the sales clerks around, and said: "Talk to me if you have something to say. Do not terrify the child." </seg>
<seg id="27"> She took the little girl with her and walked out of the bookstore after she paid out several dozen Yuan as a fine, while the sales clerks were whispering reluctantly. Then, she could clearly see the face messed with tears and panic. </seg>
<seg id="28"> She smiled, and brought the little girl home. She cleaned her up thoroughly and let her go without asking anything. </seg>
<seg id="29"> She especially urged her before she left, "If you want to read books, you could come here, auntie's home has a lot of books." </seg>
<seg id="30"> The little girl, who was still in a panic, gazed at her deeply before running away, and never showed up again. </seg>
<seg id="31"> Time passes as quickly as running water, and a period of ten years has passed in a flash without notice. </seg>
<seg id="32"> She had forgotten the thing a long time ago, and still lives there with a calm and serene life. </seg>
<seg id="33"> One afternoon, knocking noises came from outside the door. </seg>
<seg id="34"> A young and strange girl with a pretty face appeared when she opened the door. She had a big smile on her face and was holding a big pile of gifts in her hands. </seg>
<seg id="35"> "Who are you looking for?" </seg>
<seg id="36"> She asked with doubt. </seg>
<seg id="37"> The girl was moved and talked with a lot of words. </seg>
<seg id="38"> It was not easy for her to find out from the strange girl's talking that she was the little girl of that year. Ten years after, she had graduated from a university without any difficulties, and now she had made a special trip to see her. </seg>
<seg id="39"> The young girl said with a soft voice and tears in her eyes: "Although I still don't understand why you were willing to pretend to be my mom and save me, during these 10 years, I have always felt that I want to call you mom." </seg>
<seg id="40"> The teacher's eyes also started to become blurred. </seg>
<seg id="41"> "If I did not help you that day, what was going to happen to you?" She asked with curiosity. </seg>
