<seg id="3"> The Sword of Righteousness: Outlook for 2006 </seg>
<seg id="4"> Author: Sword of Righteousness </seg>
<seg id="5"> I remember that at the beginning of 2005 Hong Kong's Apple Daily carried an article titled "Falun Rotates Continuously and Its Gong May Be Able to Defeat a Regime". </seg>
<seg id="6"> The article states that 2004 was a year in which Falun Gong advanced triumphantly. </seg>
<seg id="7"> The article lists examples of various occasions and situations where suppression of the Falun Gong movement by mainland China's overseas officials failed and relates how Falun Gong practitioners speaking the truth around the world have caused mainland China to completely lose face. </seg>
<seg id="8"> But 2004 doesn't seem to have been anything special when compared to the powerful momentum of 2005's Withdraw-from-the-Party Movement, which was caused by the book Nine Commentaries on the Communist Party. </seg>
<seg id="9"> So, what will 2006 bring? </seg>
<seg id="10"> We can probably get a hint of how this year will develop from two events that occurred at the start of the year. </seg>
<seg id="11"> One was the publication of "On Eliminating Evil" by the creator of Falun Gong. The article pronounced that, following July 20, 1999, the final days of mainland China's secret agents were nigh. </seg>
<seg id="12"> As for this article, many people may half believe it or disbelieve it. </seg>
<seg id="13"> But regardless of whether it is believed or not, history and facts will prove it! </seg>
<seg id="14"> Of course, the Chinese Communist Party's secret agents are like rats that live in the sewers. </seg>
<seg id="15"> Their "natural or accidental" death will not attract the attention of society and public opinion. </seg>
<seg id="16"> But the large scale striking down or repentance of the CCP's overseas secret agents will inevitably deliver a heavy blow and a great shock to the power-wielding strata of the CCP. </seg>
<seg id="17"> Frightened by the awe-inspiring threat of being struck down, they have no choice but to carefully consider their own means of escape and survival---withdrawing from the Party, defecting and fighting against the CCP. </seg>
<seg id="18"> For this reason, the CCP's "ultra-stable bureaucratic organization", held together by squalid self interest, will start to move toward shakiness, disintegration and collapse! </seg>
<seg id="19"> Another event was the human-rights hunger-strike protest movement launched by Gao Zhisheng. </seg>
<seg id="20"> It erupted suddenly and initially wasn't well-regarded, but it unexpectedly received an enthusiastic response from around the world as well as a collective response from people from all walks of life and various influential bodies. </seg>
<seg id="21"> If this movement can become a bond bringing together the suffering people and various influential bodies fighting for justice, and can be made stronger, then there might be hope that the outside force that deals the final blow to  the CCP, an evil regime in a very precarious situation, may take shape from here. </seg>
<seg id="22"> If it can be said that 2005 was the year that the Communist Party was destroyed at the spiritual level, then in 2006 things will have entered into the stage where the Communist Party is destroyed at the spiritual and material level. </seg>
<seg id="23"> Following further dissemination of the Nine Commentaries and growth in the wave of withdrawals from the party, the disintegration of the CCP and the consolidation of external forces fighting for justice, the countdown has begun for the end of the lifespan of the fiendish CCP! </seg>
<seg id="24"> The will of heaven and the will of the people have merged. The strength of the spirits and the strength of man are joining together. </seg>
<seg id="25"> The heavenly sword is pointing straight at the demon CCP! </seg>
<seg id="26"> If it can be said that 2004 was a year of marching forward in militant song and 2005 was a year of moving forward with great momentum, then what will be the closing assessment of  2006? </seg>
<seg id="27"> I hope it is an earthshaking radical change and triumphant return in victory! </seg>
